    dc:description "Figure 1. Chironomus (Benthalia) hamatus. Paratype male: a) gonocoxite and gonostylus (slightly crushed subapically); b) hypopygium remains; c) Head; d) Head section showing frontal tubercles and warts. Scale bars = 100 µm." ;
